# FijiCabConnect

Cab booking platform for Fiji — driver app (Expo), passenger app (Expo), admin panel (Next.js), Node.js backend.

## TypeScript & Imports

- Strict mode, zero `any` types — use `unknown` + type guards
- Absolute imports only: `@/components`, `@/lib`, `@/utils`
- Do NOT modify `tsconfig.json` or `next.config.js` without explicit permission

## Security (Non-Negotiable)

- Secrets in `.env` only — never commit credentials
- Validate ALL user inputs; sanitize before DB writes
- Auth required on all protected endpoints
- Rate limit public APIs
- CSRF tokens on forms; CSP headers for XSS

## Icons

- **React Native apps:** `.png` only for `<Image source={}>` — SVGs are React components, NOT image assets
- **Admin (Next.js):** prefer SVG
- New icons → add file to `assets/icons/` AND register in `constants/index.ts`

## Prohibited

- Mock / static data — always use real backend
- Hardcoded config values — use env vars
- `node_modules` hotfixes without a `patch-package` patch
- Direct `android/` or `ios/` dir edits — use Expo config plugins
- Package versions that drift from Expo-supported ranges
